President Uhuru Kenyatta has eulogized veteran journalist Hillary Ng&rsquo;weno as a distinguished Kenyan whose role in shaping the media industry will be remembered for generations. Ng&rsquo;weno who died yesterday at the age of 83, was the man behind the weekly review, a magazine that broke new frontiers in news reporting in the late 70&rsquo;s, the &rsquo;80s and 90&rsquo;s. &nbsp;But what made Hillary Ng&rsquo;weno an icon in the media industry?
